import React from 'react'; const Welcome = ({ onD3React, onQGIS, onFinish }) => { return (

HI!

The data visualization is about travel experience with different transportation modes. The static map and interactive map data visualization were created and developed by Quantum Geographic Information System (QGIS) software and D3.js with React respectively. In this visualization, you can find the data regarding HRV, HR_mad, stress level, and journey satisfaction score during the travel.

First, you will explore QGIS map and then d3.js React map. You need to gain the information as much as you can. There is no limited time on this experiment, and you can make your own notes. Once you finished with the map click the questionnaire button and fill in the form.

After complete of the two questionnaires, then you can click the "Finish" button.

Here is the step of this experiment:

  • Explore QGIS map
  • Fill in the first questionnaire
  • Explore d3.js React Map
  • Fill in the second questionnaire

); }; export default Welcome;
